Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Chop the @potato{2} into wedges about the length 
and width of your index finger and put on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle a good glug of 
@oil{}, sprinkle over a pinch of @salt{} and pop on the top shelf of your oven for 
~{30-35%minutes}, or until browned and slightly crispy.

Meanwhile, put each @British chicken breasts{4} in a #bowl{} and pour over two-thirds 
of the @BBQ sauce{6}, a good pinch of @salt{} and a grind of @black pepper{}. Mix 
together with your hands to ensure your chicken gets a good coating of BBQ sauce. 
Wrap a @streaky bacon rasher{4} around each chicken breast (see picture) and place 
on a baking tray. If you have any BBQ sauce left in the bowl, scrape it out onto the 
top of your chicken.

Pop your chicken in your oven, on the middle shelf for ~{25-30%minutes}.  

> Tip: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

While your chicken and wedges are cooking, you can get on with the baked beans! 
Cut the @onion{1} in half through the root, peel and chop into 1cm pieces. Put your 
onion in a #frying pan{} with a drizzle of @oil{} on medium heat and cook for 
~{5%minutes}. Drain, rinse and add the @cannellini beans{1}. Once your onion is 
soft, add the @smoked paprika{1.5} and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @tomato passata{1}, fill the empty carton three-quarters full with 
@water{3/4%carton} and add this as well. Sprinkle in a pinch of @salt{}, a good grind 
of @black pepper{} and mix everything together. Simmer gently for ~{7%minutes}, 
then remove from the heat, add the @baby spinach{1} and pop a #lid{} on. Leave to 
the side for ~{5-7%minutes} until your spinach has wilted, then stir it through.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{80}. As soon as your chicken is cooked, remove 
from your oven and move your potato wedges to the middle shelf. Preheat your #grill{} 
to high. Divide your cheese evenly between each chicken breast then place under 
your grill for ~{3-5%minutes} or until your cheese is browned and bubbly.

Serve your chicken with your potato wedges and homemade baked beans on the side. 
Enjoy!